length() → Returns the number of characters in the string.

charAt(int index) → Returns character at the given index.

toCharArray() → Converts string into a character array.

equals(Object another) → Compares content of two strings.

equalsIgnoreCase(String another) → Compares strings ignoring case.

compareTo(String another) → Lexicographically compares two strings.

contains(CharSequence s) → Checks if substring exists.

startsWith(String prefix) → Checks if string starts with given prefix.

endsWith(String suffix) → Checks if string ends with given suffix.

indexOf(String str) → Returns index of first occurrence of substring.

lastIndexOf(String str) → Returns index of last occurrence.

substring(int begin, int end) → Extracts part of the string.

subSequence(int begin, int end) → Similar to substring but returns CharSequence.

replace(char oldChar, char newChar) → Replaces all occurrences of a char.

replace(CharSequence target, CharSequence replacement) → Replaces all substrings.

replaceAll(String regex, String replacement) → Replaces substrings using regex.

replaceFirst(String regex, String replacement) → Replaces first match of regex.

trim() → Removes leading and trailing spaces.

strip() → Removes Unicode whitespaces (Java 11+).

stripLeading() → Removes leading whitespaces only.

stripTrailing() → Removes trailing whitespaces only.

toLowerCase() → Converts to lowercase.

toUpperCase() → Converts to uppercase.

split(String regex) → Splits string into array by regex.

join(CharSequence delimiter, CharSequence... elements) → Joins multiple strings with delimiter.

valueOf(Object obj) → Converts object to string.

format(String format, Object... args) → Returns formatted string.

intern() → Stores string in String Pool and returns reference.

matches(String regex) → Checks if string matches regex.
